<p>
	Contrail is re-defining how networks are built and operated with our Virtualized Network Control solution. Our Datapath Engineers are developing a core piece of technology where every CPU cycle matters - it is all about performance! You will be developing a significantly improved packet forwarding module within virtualization technologies like KVM, Xen, Linux Containers, VMWare, etc.</p>
<p>
	Responsibilities:<br />
	Work with Architecture team to refine the System Specifications and identify the development approach<br />
	Create specifications for software modules that are Highly Available and perform at a blistering pace<br />
	Develop/implement Control Plane and Data Plane protocols<br />
	Create Automated Test Environment in-concert with software modules</p>
<p>
	Qualifications:<br />
	BS in Computer Science or equivalent.<br />
	Hands on development experience in Linux kernel<br />
	Experience in switching or routing datapath software development<br />
	Familiarity with Server Virtualization technologies like KVM, Xen<br />
	Extensive experience in C/C++, Python, and/or Perl<br />
	Experience with vSwitch development like OVS or equivalent<br />
	Experience with network ACLs and stateful firewall<br />
	Knowledge of a unicast and multicast routing protocols like OSPF, PIM</p>
