<p>
	Responsibilities:<br />
	- Lead and execute Linux kernel development in the area of, Device Drivers, Hardware Interfaces, Virtualization, storage stack and Networking stack.<br />
	- Develop rapid prototypes and proof of concepts of and architectures.<br />
	- Get resolution on critical issues involving packet forwarding path.<br />
	- Get involved in all phases of software development and support including requirements, design, coding, unit test and performance tuning.</p>
<p>
	Skills:<br />
	- BS/MS in Computer Science or equivalent.<br />
	- Extensive development experience of Linux kernel<br />
	- Indept knowledge of TCP/IP stack, Network interface card architectures, Network IO concepts, and Virtualization.<br />
	- Knowledge of file system and memory management.&nbsp;<br />
	- Knowledge of one of virtualization technologies (KVM, Hyper-V or VMware ESX)<br />
	- Exposure to Open vSwitch and/or OpenStack a plus.</p>
